            <thetext>A user reported this:

In an on-line tutorial for &quot;Brightmail&quot; I discovered what appears to be a sieve filter for cidr formatted ip ranges:

if envelope :comparator &quot;i;ip-mask&quot; &quot;peerip&quot; [&quot;104.140.0.0/16&quot;, &quot;104.206.0.0/16&quot;]{
        fileinto &quot;INBOX.Junk Mail&quot;; stop;
}

I suppose this would appear in the require list as &quot;comparator-i;ip-mask&quot;

====

I think this is a Dovecot specific option, but we can look at supporting it in Cyrus as well.</thetext>
